cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EL, cs.AR, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses hardware neural networks and deep learning algorithms. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper deals with analog resistive synapses, which are an emerging technology in the field of hardware neural networks. 
- cs.EL (Electronics) is another possible category as the paper discusses the engineering of activation functions and threshold weight update schemes, which are related to the design of electronic circuits. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a relevant category as the paper deals with the design of hardware neural networks based on analog resistive synapses. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the classification accuracy of the MNIST handwritten digit dataset.
